                        <div class="help-text">
                            <h2 id="faq_control_panel">Control Panel</h2>
                                <button class="accordion">How do I change the mode?</button>
                                    <div class="panel">
                                        <p class="p-help">
                                            In VentPro it is possible to change between <b></b>automatic</b> and <b>manual mode</b>.
                                            This is possible by switching the button on the control panel page.
                                        </p>
                                        <img src="../public/img/help-images/change-mode.png">
                                    </div>
                                <button class="accordion">What is the <b>difference</b> between <b>automatic</b> mode and <b>manual</b> mode?</button>
                                    <div class="panel"> 
                                        <p class="p-help">
                                            In <b>automatic mode</b> it is possible to set the <b>pressure</b> of the ventilaton controller
                                            to a targeted pressure between 0 Pa and 120 Pa.
                                            In <b>manual mode</b> however it is possible to set the <b>fan speed</b> of the ventilation controller to a targeted speed 
                                            between 0% and 100%. 
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                <button class="accordion">How do I change the <b>target pressure</b>?</button>
                                    <div class="panel">
                                            <p class="p-help">
                                                The target pressure can only be adjusted in automatic mode. To do this, the slider must be moved to the desired target value. It is possible to choose a value between 0 Pa und 120 Pa. 
                                                Once you stop moving the handle the system will automatically set the pressure to the targeted value. If the targeted pressure is not reached within a reasonable time there is a notification. 
                                                The current pressure is always written above the graph.
                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                    <button class="accordion">How is the <b>pressure</b> monitored?</button>
                                        <div class="panel">
                                            <p class="p-help">
                                                The current pressure can be viewed in automatic mode. There, the current pressure is displayed as well as pressure changes overtime within a graph.
                                                With the buttons underneath the graph it is possible to switch between all data, data from the current day or the last minute.
                                                Hovering over the graph displays the pressure at the corresponding time.
                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                    <button class="accordion">How is the <b>fan speed changed</b>?</button>
                                        <div class="panel">
                                                <p class="p-help">
                                                    The fan speed can only be adjusted in manual mode. To do this, the slider must be moved to the desired target value. It is possible to choose a value between 0% und 100%. 
                                                    Once you stop moving the handle the system will automatically set the fan speed to the targeted value. If the targeted speed is not reached within a reasonable time there is a notification. 
                                                    The current fan speed is always written above the graph.
                                                </p>
                                            </div>
                                        <button class="accordion">How is the <b>fan speed monitored</b>?</button>
                                            <div class="panel">
                                                <p class="p-help">
                                                    The current fan speed can be viewed in manual mode. There, the current fan speed is displayed as well as changes in the fan speed overtime within a graph.
                                                    With the buttons underneath the graph it is possible to switch between all data, data from the current day or the last minute.
                                                    Hovering over the graph displays the fan speed at the corresponding time.
                                                </p>
                                            </div>
                                        <br>
                            <h2 id="faq_settings">Settings</h2>
                                <button class="accordion">How do I <b>change</b> my <b>password</b>?</button>
                                    <div class="panel">
                                        <p class="p-help">
                                                The password can be changed in the <a href="/settings">settings</a> section. There you should enter the new password and confirm 
                                                it by clicking the button.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                <button class="accordion">What is shwon in <b>log activity</b>?</button>
                                    <div class="panel"> 
                                        <p class="p-help">
                                                If you are logged in as admin, you can see in the log-in activities which users have logged in and when. 
                                                So it is possible to see when changes were made to the settings of the ventilation controller.  
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                <button class="accordion">How do I add a <b>new user</b>?</button>
                                    <div class="panel">
                                        <p class="p-help">
                                                If you are logged in as admin you have the possibility to add a new user. 
                                                For this you only have to enter a username and a password and confirm it with a click on the button. 
                                                The password should be changed at the first login of the new user.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                            
        
                               
